# Labeled set for the accuracy report — copy this file to `labels.txt`
# (next to it, NOT a rename) and fill in the handles you have an opinion
# on. `config/labels.txt` is gitignored; this `.example` is the
# checked-in template.
#
# ============================================================
# Format
# ============================================================
#
#   <handle> keep    # account belongs in the Keep bucket
#   <handle> drop    # account belongs in the Unfollow bucket
#
# `#` starts a comment to end-of-line. Blank lines are fine. Duplicate
# handles are a HARD error — silent dedup would hide a typo. The label
# `review` is intentionally NOT supported: review is "I haven't decided",
# and a label means "I have decided".
#
# When `config/labels.txt` exists, `ig-mgr` prints a confusion matrix
# (label × bucket) after the standard report, plus a per-account list
# of hard mismatches (label=keep ∩ bucket=unfollow OR
# label=drop ∩ bucket=keep). Soft mismatches (anything involving
# `review`) are visible in the matrix but not listed.
#
# ============================================================
# Recommended labeling strategy
# ============================================================
#
# Aim for ~30 labels — that's where the confusion matrix gets useful
# without the labeling itself becoming the time sink. Best distribution:
#
#   - 5 labels at the very TOP of `keep_prob` (top-5 in the Markdown
#     summary). These should all be obvious keeps for you. If any of
#     these come back as label=keep & bucket=review or worse, the
#     weights are broken in an obvious way.
#
#   - 5 labels at the very BOTTOM of `keep_prob` (bottom-5 in the
#     Markdown summary). These should all be obvious drops. Same
#     calibration role for the other end.
#
#   - 20 labels from the REVIEW band (keep_prob ~0.3-0.7) — the
#     discriminative cases where you actually have an opinion. This
#     is where weight tuning moves accounts and where the confusion
#     matrix earns its keep.
#
# Open `recommendations_<DATE>.md` from a recent run, pick handles
# you have a strong feeling about, paste them below. The Markdown
# summary already shows `display_name` and `dominant_feature` so
# you have context without opening Instagram.
#
# ============================================================
# Example entries
# ============================================================

# best_friend_irl      keep
# college_roommate     keep
# brand_account_xyz    drop
# follow_for_follow    drop
